		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Data Protection Directive</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub">&nbsp;&nbsp;(Redirected from <a href="/w/index.php?title=Directive_95/46/EC_on_the_protection_of_personal_data&amp;redirect=no" title="Directive 95/46/EC on the protection of personal data">Directive 95/46/EC on the protection of personal data</a>)</div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<p>The <b>Data Protection Directive</b> (officially Directive 95/46/EC on the protection of individuals with regard to the processing of personal data and on the free movement of such data) is a <a href="/wiki/European_Union_directive" title="European Union directive" class="mw-redirect">European Union directive</a> which regulates the processing of personal data within the <a href="/wiki/European_Union" title="European Union">European Union</a>. It is an important component of EU <a href="/wiki/Privacy_law" title="Privacy law">privacy</a> and <a href="/wiki/Human_rights_law" title="Human rights law" class="mw-redirect">human rights</a> law. The directive was implemented in 1995 by the <a href="/wiki/European_Commission" title="European Commission">European Commission</a>.</p>
<table id="toc" class="toc" summary="Contents">
